# HTTP Handlers

HTTP request handlers that serve the Dora Ethereum beacon chain explorer web interface and API endpoints.

## Key Integration Patterns
- Use `InitPageData()` for consistent page initialization with common template data
- Integrate with `services.GlobalBeaconService` for all beacon chain data access
- Implement caching via `services.GlobalFrontendCache.ProcessCachedPage()` for performance
- Support rate limiting through `services.GlobalCallRateLimiter.CheckCallLimit()`

## Response Architecture  
- Separate data building (`build*PageData`) from request handling for reusability
- Use template-based HTML rendering with Go templates for web pages
- Return structured JSON responses for API endpoints
- Implement lazy loading patterns for tabbed interfaces

## Error Handling
- Use `handlePageError()` for consistent error page responses
- Use `handleTemplateError()` for template execution error handling
- Provide user-friendly error messages with appropriate HTTP status codes
- Support both HTML error pages and JSON error responses